\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 
Did she ever go out visiting friends or out to enjoy herself at all and your father would sort of look after the family while she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 No, she'd go - she'd go to relations - to relations and - just - for her - for her tea or something of that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 And your father would look after the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Well - that would be after we got older, we could look after ourselves a bit you see. But he - he'd - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid664984\charrsid13133166 help}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166  look to the meal. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7561684\charrsid13133166 
Then I had a sister - I had sister, she's now seventy-two or seventy-three, well - she'd usually - help me father with the meals. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 
We never helped. No. Aye, we never helped. The girls did it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 You don't think your father would take charge of the family while you were all small?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Oh no, me mother - left to me mother like,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 When you were young before you left school do you remember having any jobs that you had to carry out regularly in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 None of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 No. Oh - the girls would. The boys didn't - we didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Do you remember what sort of jobs the girls would do about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Well the - no - I can't, you see, the - the two youngest - a lot - well - a lot younger than me altoge
ther. But me sister, she used to have her jobs to do but - we - we never had, me mother never bothered us with anything like that. We'd run errands if that was any - aye, aye. We'd run errands for her, aye, and used to take me father's dinner, when he wer
e working you see. He were always on piece work, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7561684\charrsid13133166 
He was always - always on piecework and I used to take him his dinners and sometimes - say it were - what we call Parish Feast Holidays, you know, and - I might sit there and he'd get his dinner and 
I'd sit till he finished but - in those days you see, they didn't - he didn't - he didn't have an hour for dinnertime. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 
He just had - he just had his dinner and then have a smoke and then he'd start work again. Well I - it was hard work, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Do you re
member the older children in the family helping the younger children with things they found difficult such as dressing or eating or anything like that?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 No - our Sarah Ann, me sister would help with the children but - when I were younger I'd - come o
n - walk on street like with a pram. With the 1 with the youngest in sometimes. I'd go on Spring Bank with a pram, I can remember that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 So you'd take a little one for a walk with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Aye, aye, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 And your sister would help the smaller ones with dressing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Do you remember the younger children helping the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7561684\charrsid13133166 older}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166  in any way at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Well - oh no, you see - there's so much difference in our ages. In fact, the two youngest - the two youngest sisters, the two sis
ters, younger sisters, can hardly tell of me being at home. You see, I went to - I went - I went into the Army 1914 well - me - me youngest sister now she's sixty-seven 1914 that's fifty six year ago isn't it. Well she'd only be one year old. Now - the ne
x
t was a brother, Frank, he'd be three, our Annie'd be five when I went into the Army. Well I went into the Army, I were in - I were in 'til January 1919, I came out in 1919 and we were married in May. So, they oft - they often say - like - they can't tell
 of me being at home hardly you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 You'd be more like an uncle to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 That's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 
Do you remember having to go to bed at a certain time in the evening when you were small, was there a fixed time that you had to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Oh no, not a fixed time but - you hadn't to be up late. Me father just - bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 So you don't remember what time it would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 When you were little did your mother put you to bed or someone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Oh yes, me mother - me mother 
- mother was the ruler in our house you see, aye. If - say - anything - ask me father about anything he'd say - and he were a Yorkshireman, he'd say, see the mother. You see. And of course it were her that her that settled things that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 How old would you be when you started to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Oh I don't know - seven or eight. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Did you share your bedroom with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Yes. With me brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 With the next eldest brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Yes, yes. We always slept together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Do you remember the sleeping arrangements of the whole family until 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 
Where everyone slept? Well the girls - the first as I say - you see, 1914 when I joined the Army there were three little ones, you see. Now - me eldest }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7561684\charrsid13133166 sister\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166  sleep by herself I 
think. And - our Frank'd sleep with one of the other boys - no, the two - the - the - me and - both - both us - both - me and the next eldest joined the Army, you see, so therefore that made more room. Well there were two - the two next boys slept togethe
r and then the youngest boy'd sleep by himself. Yes, he'd sleep by himself - I think. I can't tell much about that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 What about during the year or two before you went in the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 You would have your own bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Oh yes. Me and 
me brother that - the other two had a bedroom, then the girls had a bedroom, like the oldest girl had a bedroom. And then the parents had a bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Were the little ones in with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Well, the baby - the baby always were, you see, in those days, they - they slept with the parents, 'til they were so old you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 In the bedroom that you shared with your brother did you have one double bed for the two of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Was there just a big bed where the girls slept?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 They had a - they were all big beds. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7561684\charrsid13133166 Aye}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 , big beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 In the kitchen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Did you have a zinc bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 How often would you do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Did you have a set time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Certainly, every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Would there be a set night for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Friday night, mostly. Aye. Aye.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 You'd all have a bath Friday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 When would you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Oh after every bath, with the bath. You put clean clothes on after your}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid664984\charrsid13133166 
 bath}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Every Friday night you'd have all clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Where did you all have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 In the house. In the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Not in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 No, in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room? Was there any occasions when you would eat in the kitchen instead of in the house?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Well it - there were - it was - it was a - a fair long kitchen and it - sometimes but it was only sometimes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Would this be because your mother was in a hurry or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Probably. Aye, probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Did your mother do all the cooking in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 What sort of equipment did she have, did she have a fire range or did she have a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 She had a range, fire range - a range - open, aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 She didn't have a gas cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 No. She had the oven and - aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 And she put pans on the fire sort of in front?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Yes. Yes. She'd have a gas - she'd have a gas.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 A gas ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 What time would you have breakfast when you were still at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Before I left school? Oh {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 Who would be present for breakfast, would your father be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 No, he started {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6240188 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 He didn't come home for his breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14512253 PS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16188304\charrsid13133166 No. We didn't see him again 'til night.
